["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name from Charnock Richard or Heath Charnock in southern Lancashire, which are probably named with a derivative of Celtic <i>carn</i> ‘cairn, pile of stones’ (see   Cairns  ).","Americanized form of Slovak <b>Černok</b>, a variant of <b>Černík</b> (see   Cernik  )."]},{"name":"Kearns","meanings":["Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Céirín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Céirín</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>ciar</i> ‘dark, black’, with the addition of English excrescent <i>-s</i>.","in Ulster, possibly a variant of   Cairns  ."]},{"name":"Carnes","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Cairns   or sometimes <b>Carins</b>, a variant of   Caron  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>.","English and Cornish: in southern England a variant of   Carn  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish: variant of   Kearns  ."]},{"name":"Kieran","meanings":["Irish (Louth and Monaghan): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Ciaráin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ciarán</i>’, a byname from a diminutive of <i>ciar</i> ‘dark, black-haired’. Variants <i>Ó Cearáin</i> and <i>Ó Céirín</i> exist in Irish, see also   Kearns  . The personal name <i>Ciarán</i> was borne by two Irish saints, a hermit of the 5th century and the founder of the monastery at Clonmacnoise (died 547)."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["Pet form of   Christopher ;  also of   Katherine   and its variants. In the medieval period it was a pet form of   Christian   and   Christiana ."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Catherine Cairns was born about 1355, in Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Duncan Cairns of that Ilk, was 20 and her mother, Ann Seaver, was 20. She married Stephen Crichton of Cairns - Sheriff of Linlithgow, Lord Erskine in 1380, in Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 6 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"umbes 1355–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1350–1433":"1350–1433","1374–1439":"1374–1439","1381–1381":"1381–1381","1382–1454":"1382–1454","1387–Male":"1387–Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1393–Male":"1393–Surnud","–1476":"–1476","1336–1390":"1336–1390","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","1393":"1393","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1390":"1390","1336":"1336","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1433":"1433","1476":"1476","1454":"1454","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","1439":"1439","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"noin 1355–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1350–1433":"1350–1433","1374–1439":"1374–1439","1381–1381":"1381–1381","1382–1454":"1382–1454","1387–Male":"1387–Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1393–Male":"1393–Kuollut","–1476":"–1476","1336–1390":"1336–1390","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","1393":"1393","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1390":"1390","1336":"1336","Abt 1355":"noin 1355","1433":"1433","1476":"1476","1454":"1454","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","1439":"1439","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Sk